                     <p class="text-sm mt-4 text-center">A typical cycle lasts 52-56 weeks, after which production declines and flocks are replaced.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#F5A42E] mb-4 text-center">Broiler Chickens: Meat Production</h3>
                    <p class="mb-6 text-center">Genetically selected for rapid growth, broilers reach market weight in a fraction of the time. The focus is on feed conversion and muscle gain.</p>
                     <div class="relative pt-1">
                        <div class="flex mb-2 items-center justify-between">
                            <div><span class="text-xs font-semibold inline-block py-1 px-2 uppercase rounded-full text-green-600 bg-green-200">Full Growth Cycle</span></div>
