                        </div>
                        <div class="overflow-hidden h-4 mb-4 text-xs flex rounded bg-green-200">
                            <div style="width:100%" class="shadow-none flex flex-col text-center whitespace-nowrap text-white justify-center bg-green-500"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                     <p class="text-sm mt-4 text-center">Broilers reach a market weight of 1.8-3.5 kg in just a few weeks, a testament to genetic selection and optimized nutrition.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="housing" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-[#0A2B4C] mb-2">Engineered Environments</h2>
            <p class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">Poultry housing is a science. From space allocation to climate control, every detail is engineered to maximize health, welfare, and productivity.</p>
            
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 mb-8">
                 <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0A2B4C] mb-4 text-center">Space Per Bird: A Critical Metric</h3>
                 <p class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">The amount of space directly impacts bird welfare and performance. Standards vary significantly based on the production system, with free-range and cage-free systems providing more room to encourage natural behaviors.</p>
                 <div class="chart-container h-[400px] max-h-[450px]"><canvas id="housingSpaceChart"></canvas></div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <div class="kpi-value">~70°F</div>
                    <div class="kpi-label">Optimal Temperature</div>
                    <p class="text-xs mt-2">The thermoneutral zone (65-75°F) where adult birds are most comfortable and productive.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <div class="kpi-value">1.5-2.0</div>
                    <div class="kpi-label">Summer Ventilation (CFM/lb)</div>
                    <p class="text-xs mt-2">Crucial for removing heat and preventing heat stress during warm months.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <div class="kpi-value">16-17</div>
                    <div class="kpi-label">Light Hours for Layers</div>
                    <p class="text-xs mt-2">Long daylight hours are essential to stimulate and maintain consistent egg production.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <div class="kpi-value">&lt;25 ppm</div>
                    <div class="kpi-label">Max Ammonia Level</div>
                    <p class="text-xs mt-2">Good ventilation and dry litter are key to keeping this toxic gas at safe levels.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
